cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

The paper proposes new techniques for training GANs to improve the quality of generated samples and alleviate mode collapse. These techniques involve regularization and alignment of distributions, which are common topics in machine learning and specifically in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of manifold learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Taylor approximations, which is related to the sub-category of cs.SD (Systems and Control).
